It's been 10 years since the Sandy Hook Elementary School tragedy here in my hometown in Connecticut.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
I had the privilege of meeting Scarlett Lewis a few months later, who tragically lost her 6-year-old son Jesse Lewis on that unimaginable day. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
I joined her in her home and we tapped together. To this day, Scarlett still credits Tapping as one of the keys that jumpstarted her healing from this unimaginable trauma.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Soon after losing her son, Scarlett was inspired to find a way to address the root cause of the suffering that leads to these kinds of horrific events. So, she founded the Jesse Lewis Choose Love Movement. 💛​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
✨ The mission of the Choose Love Movement is to offer free, evidence-based, comprehensive social emotional development for schools, homes, and communities. ✨​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
I’ve been so honored to support Scarlett’s work over the past 10 years, and to help her incorporate Tapping into these powerful, transformational programs. I am a complete fan of @ChooseLoveMovement and all it is doing to make our world a better, more loving place. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
➡️ Today I also want to give us all an opportunity to take action in a meaningful way so that we can continue to work towards building a more loving world together.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
I highly encourage you to check out the link in my bio or stories so you can learn more about Scarlett’s mission and support this amazing cause.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
💛 Let's all choose love today. 💛

So much of who we are as adults... who we believe ourselves to be, what we believe about the world, how we feel emotions like love, fear, happiness, guilt, and how we relate to others... comes from how adults in our childhood, especially our parents, spoke to us.

And unfortunately for many, that language was negative and hurt our confidence, self worth, and ability to learn and grow as adults.

But as this video shows, healing can occur. We can use Tapping to, step-by-step, release decades of trauma from our body and mind.

Bobbie is an amazing person who transformed her life with Tapping. She’s a beautiful reminder to us all of what’s possible in our own lives. ✨

Just as my body needs me to feed it nourishing foods to stay well, my mind also needs to be fed in a nourishing way.​​​​​​​​
 ​​​​​​​​
We are making choices every single day when it comes to what we feed our minds. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
❗️All day long, all the people and things we interact with – they become a part of us. From our friends to our coworkers… from the social media posts we scroll through, to the TV shows we choose to watch… They all influence us and shape us and affect who we are and how we feel.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Be sure that what you are engaging with is truly nourishing for you and supports who you want to become… Be sure it helps you feel your best, making you feel inspired, motivated, encouraged, lifted up, grateful, and joyful.​​​​​​​​
 ​​​​​​​​
✅ Choose content, choose people, choose conversations that make you feel your best today!​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
And have a great day! 🤗

It always amazes me how much power our mindsets hold. 🙌⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The way we think about things can have a profound influence on how we feel and how we walk through life.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
And sometimes, it comes down to the simplest of shifts in language… the subtlest changes in the words we use to frame our experience.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Author James Clear recently offered these beautiful and simple mindset shifts. He shared:⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“I’m not hurt, I’m healing.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’m not losing, I’m learning.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I was not rejected, I was redirected.”⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
➡️ The difference in one to the other is subtle. However, those simple changes in language – from hurt to healing, from losing to learning, from rejected to redirected – they transform the perspective in extremely powerful ways.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The way we think about things, the way we speak about them, the language we use – it really does matter.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So, let’s consider – where in our own lives might we benefit from trying out simple mindset shifts? Where in our own lives might a subtle change in language or wording help us think about a situation in a whole new way?⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
💭 Maybe you’ve been thinking “I’m stuck,” but you can try reframing that to: “I’m figuring out how to move forward.”⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
💭 Maybe you’ve been thinking “I failed!” but you can try reframing that to: “I’m learning so much.”⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
💭 Maybe you’ve been thinking “I’m behind,” but you can try reframing that to: “I’m moving at my own pace.”⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Try out some of these subtle, but powerful, mindset shifts today and see how your day transforms!⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

The Harvard Study of Adult Development is considered to be the world’s longest scientific study on happiness. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
➡️ So far, it has been going on for 85 years, following the participants from their teenage years into old age.​​​​​​​​
 ​​​​​​​​
Tons of data has been collected over the years and analyzed to help us answer this question: ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
❓What makes for a happy and healthy life?​​​​​​​​
 ​​​​​​​​
One single thing 😱 has surfaced time and time again as an answer to that question.​​​​​​​​
 ​​​​​​​​
💬 As two leaders of the study, Robert Waldinger and March Schulz, put it:​​​​​​​​
 ​​​​​​​​
“Through all the years of studying these lives, one crucial factor stands out for the consistency and power of its ties to physical health, mental health, and longevity. Contrary to what many people might think, it’s not career achievement, or exercise, or a healthy diet. Don’t get us wrong; these things matter (a lot). But one thing continuously demonstrates its broad and enduring importance: Good relationships.​​​​​​​​
 ​​​​​​​​
In fact, good relationships are significant enough that if we had to take all eighty-four years of the Harvard Study and boil it down to a single principle for living, one life investment that is supported by similar findings across a wide variety of other studies, it would be this: Good relationships keep us healthier and happier. Period.​​​​​​​​
 ​​​​​​​​
So if you’re going to make that one choice to best ensure your own health and happiness, science tells us that your choice should be to cultivate warm relationships.”​​​​​​​​
 ​​​​​​​​
👋 So today, make an investment in your own health and happiness. Focus on connection and tend to your relationships. It’s an investment that appears to be well worth your while. 😉

In the midst of life’s whirlwind, when we are dealing with so much, we need to consciously choose to take a moment to relax and breathe deeply, and to remember that we don’t need to carry the weight of the world on our shoulders. 🌎

It’s okay to hit pause when you’re overwhelmed! ❤️

Give yourself permission to relax and surrender, trusting that everything will ultimately fall into place. Invite greater ease and flow into your life by tapping along with me for 60 seconds. 🙏✨

⬇️ Tapping Script: ⬇️

Even though I am dealing with so much

I choose to relax and breathe deeply now

I can let go of some of this pressure

I don’t need to take on the weight of the world

I’m open to changing this pattern and releasing this burden

So I relax and begin to let go now

Trusting that everything will be okay

As I relax I breathe easier and feel lighter

I’m open to greater ease in my life

It’s safe for me to let go and allow my life to flow

Today is the 11th anniversary of the Sandy Hook Elementary School mass shooting that took place in my hometown in 2012.⁣

I had the privilege of meeting Scarlett Lewis a few days after, who tragically lost her 6-year-old son Jesse Lewis on that unimaginable day. I joined her in her home with Dr. Lori Leyden and we talked and tapped and cried together. Scarlett still credits Tapping as one of the keys that jumpstarted her healing from this unimaginable trauma.

After losing her son, Scarlett was inspired to find a way to address the root cause of the suffering that leads to these kinds of horrific events. So, she founded the Jesse Lewis Choose Love Movement. ❤️

The mission of the Choose Love Movement is to offer free, evidence-based, comprehensive social emotional development for schools, homes, and communities.

I’ve been so honored to support Scarlett’s work over the past 11 years, and to help her incorporate Tapping into these powerful, transformational programs. I am a massive fan of @ChooseLoveMovement and all it is doing to make our world a better, more loving place.

Let’s all choose love today. ❤️
